Source URLs:
- https://platform.moonshot.ai/docs/guide/use-kimi-vision-model
- https://platform.moonshot.ai/docs/guide/kimi-k2-5-quickstart
Fetched: 2026-02-27

Kimi/K2.5 vision+chat requirements:
- API base: https://api.moonshot.ai/v1
- Chat endpoint: /chat/completions
- Vision inputs must be message.content as array of parts, not JSON-stringified text.
- Supported image input: base64 image_url or uploaded file IDs.
- URL-formatted remote images are not supported.
- For kimi-k2.5 parameter behavior differs:
  - thinking default enabled; can be disabled via {"type":"disabled"}
  - temperature/top_p/n/presence_penalty/frequency_penalty are constrained; non-default values can error.
- Recommended to keep defaults for k2.5 parameters.

Implementation implications:
- Do not force temperature=0 for kimi-k2.5.
- Send vision content in structured array blocks.
- Keep a controllable thinking mode flag with safe default.
